entries.meaning: (biochemistry, genetics, organic chemistry) A nucleoside derived from adenine and ribose, found in striated muscle tissue. [from 20th c.]
examples: Caffeine acts as an antagonist at receptors in the brain for one of the chemical messengers called adenosine.
